## Section 3 - Lab Deployment Steps
---

### Step 1 – Verify Current Directory

```bash
pwd
```

#### Validation

```bash
/home/<username>
```

#### End of Step 1
---

### Step 2 – List Files

```bash
ls
```

#### Extended Listing

```bash
ls -la
```

#### End of Step 2
---

### Step 3 – Create and Open File in nano

```bash
nano my-first-note.txt
```

#### Behavior

- Creates file if it does not exist
- Opens file editor if it exists

#### End of Step 3
---

### Step 4 – Basic nano Operations

| Action | Key |
|------|------|
| Save | Ctrl + O |
| Exit | Ctrl + X |
| Cancel | Ctrl + C |

#### End of Step 4
---

### Step 5 – Viewport Navigation

| Action | Key |
|------|------|
| Page Down | PgDn |
| Page Up | PgUp |

#### Observation

Movement is dependent on terminal viewport size.

#### End of Step 5
---

### Step 6 – Search Function

```bash
Ctrl + W
```

#### Browser Limitation

Ctrl + W closes browser tab.

#### Workaround

```bash
F6
```

#### End of Step 6
---

### Step 7 – Replace Function

```bash
Ctrl + \
```

#### End of Step 7
---

### Step 8 – Word Navigation

| Action | Key |
|------|------|
| Back word | Alt + B |
| Forward word | Alt + F |

#### Issue

Browser intercepts Alt key combinations.

#### End of Step 8
---

### Step 9 – Workaround Strategy

- Use arrow keys
- Use PgUp / PgDn
- Use function keys (F6)

#### End of Step 9
